parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause the vehicle to stall, catch fire, or experience intermittent failures of various systems, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls or shuts off while driving
smoke or flames come from the hood
warning lights illuminate on the dashboard
and electrical systems such as headlights
taillights
or wipers malfunction.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition system can cause the vehicle to stall or not start, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The key gets stuck in the ignition
the ignition switch fails to turn
the vehicle won't start
and the steering wheel locks.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Door Lock and Trunk Latch Issues
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the door locks and trunk latch can cause inconvenience and safety risks, as the doors may not lock or unlock properly, and the trunk may not open or close securely.
symptoms: The doors lock or unlock randomly
the trunk latch fails to open or close
and the door locks are stuck or jammed.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the cooling system can cause the engine to overheat, leading to engine damage, stalling, or fires.
symptoms: The vehicle overheats
the temperature gauge rises
and the engine stalls or catches fire.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel pump can cause the vehicle to stall, leading to a loss of power and potentially causing accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls or hesitates
especially when driving at high speeds or when the fuel level is low
the engine surges or loses power
and the fuel pump may make a loud whining or grinding noise.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the fuel system can cause the vehicle to stall, leading to a loss of power and potentially causing accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls or hesitates
especially when driving at high speeds or when the fuel level is low
the engine surges or loses power
and the fuel system may make a loud whining or grinding noise.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the accelerator pedal can cause the vehicle to surge or lose power, leading to a loss of control and potentially causing accidents.
symptoms: The accelerator pedal sticks or feels soft
the vehicle surges or loses power
and the engine may rev unexpectedly.
